Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["\<\
Consider an end mirror that has a DC offset of \[CapitalDelta]L and is \
modulated by a length \[CapitalDelta]z cos(\[Omega] t).\
\>", "Section",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9037062597353277`*^9, 
  3.903706314666047*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"c026d8f9-a76b-4af3-884a-\
6c483c366671"],

Cell["\<\
Up until now we have worked only with carrier light at a single frequency, \
\[Omega]0
Now, when we modulate the light at the end mirror, we scatter carrier light \
into two additional audio-frequency sidebands, \[Omega]0+\[Omega] and \
\[Omega]0-\[Omega].
If those sidebands are within the bandwidth of the interferometer, those will \
also be resonantly enhanced by the cavity.
This is why you might need to know the TF from the back mirror to reflection \
in the adjacency matrix.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9037063205013943`*^9, 3.903706391054399*^9}, {
  3.903706684868381*^9, 
  3.903706764929283*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"340063d9-37b5-47f5-92e1-\
6e9e907f7500"],

