 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9037075824928207`*^9, 3.903707622098946*^9}, {
  3.90371461408225*^9, 3.90371461877571*^9}, {3.968246370999632*^9, 
  3.968246395653545*^9}, {3.9682464371889*^9, 
  3.968246462506949*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"57aeda01-0443-4661-99ad-\
87b0db299a52"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Frequency Definitions", "Subsubsection",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.968246513701357*^9, 
  3.9682465198856573`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"c865c59b-4ece-4839-9cd4-\
104ae1d2a475"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "\[Omega]0 is the carrier frequency of the main laser, often considered DC \
or 0 Hz due to the fact this term is common to all of the electric fields and \
therefore drops out of the power calculations (P = ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"|", "E", 
    SuperscriptBox["|", "2"]}], TraditionalForm]],
  FormatType->TraditionalForm,ExpressionUUID->
  "649831bf-e41b-4c11-baac-eae5ee3a62b1"],
 ")\n\[LineSeparator]\[CapitalOmega] is the RF modulation frequency applied \
to the input laser.  The RF frequency is summed or subtracted from the main \
laser frequency yield two ",
 StyleBox["RF sideband ",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 "terms ",
 "(\[Omega]0\[PlusMinus]\[CapitalOmega]).  \[LineSeparator]The RF sideband \
electric fields are usually set to be ",
 StyleBox["antiresonant",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " in the Fabry-Perot, to provide a static reference to beat against.\
\[LineSeparator]\n\[Omega] is the audio frequency of the length modulation, \
in our in our case, applied to the intracavity field incident on the end \
mirror.\[LineSeparator]This modulation creates six fields (\[Omega]0\
\[PlusMinus]\[Omega], \
\[Omega]0\[PlusMinus]\[CapitalOmega]\[PlusMinus]\[Omega]), yielding a total \
of nine fields.\[LineSeparator]These fields can either resonate or not in the \
Fabry-Perot, depending on the value of \[Omega].\nThey are created at the \
point of modulation, i.e. the end mirror, so we must grab the field transfer \
function matrix elements from ",
 StyleBox["B ",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 "above."
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.968246524181135*^9, 3.968246644648086*^9}, {
  3.968246680398932*^9, 3.968246755035277*^9}, {3.9682467990850267`*^9, 
  3.968246830961239*^9}, {3.968246904825766*^9, 3.9682470338891363`*^9}, {
  3.968247094444281*^9, 3.968247139601419*^9}, {3.968247204870326*^9, 
  3.968247285027088*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"4ace5a3c-d127-4519-9728-\
18a53ab4b15e"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Phase Consideration", "Subsubsection",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.968246498763894*^9, 
  3.968246506578498*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"10ef7cde-2d30-4d2e-bdb2-\
9269d3d6f50d"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "I make some notes here about the phase replacements done\nFirst, we always \
assume that nominally, the cavity is on resonance, i.e. ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{
     FractionBox["\[Omega]0", "c"], "L"}], "=", 
    RowBox[{"2", "\[Pi]", " ", "n"}]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "3c4a3ac1-2e09-4cf8-816b-140d0223447d"],
 ", just to make the math easier.\nAny DC offsets will be grouped into the \
\[CapitalDelta]L term\nNext, the audio frequency shaking is accounted for \
here in the \[Omega] terms, \nwhich only come into play for the \[Omega]0\
\[PlusMinus]\[Omega], \
\[Omega]0\[PlusMinus]\[CapitalOmega]\[PlusMinus]\[Omega] terms.\nHere is \
where the (L+\[CapitalDelta]L) terms will both matter, as they have different \
effects on each sideband.\nThere should be four terms: ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   FractionBox[
    RowBox[{"(", 
     RowBox[{"\[Omega]0", "+", "\[Omega]"}], ")"}], "c"], TraditionalForm]],
  ExpressionUUID->"0f186f07-36a1-448a-b182-5a0152164a28"],
 "(L+\[CapitalDelta]L), but we just said that ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{
     FractionBox["\[Omega]0", "c"], "L"}], "=", 
    RowBox[{"2", "\[Pi]", " ", "n"}]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "ce15fcdb-545e-428c-960a-2a705d6b5950"],
 ", so the phase is zero for that term, again just to make the math easier"
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.903781608973239*^9, 3.9037817587215443`*^9}, {
   3.9037818371203823`*^9, 3.903781908381192*^9}, 
   3.968247437209895*^9},ExpressionUUID->"5fa0fa91-b64e-4172-bd38-\
8b957b414f4a"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Some convenient phases for carrier, upper, and lower sidebands.  Factor is \
the random factor of 2 or ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SqrtBox["2"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "7007259a-9d61-41d5-a9c7-5f9a540bb4d6"],
 "that doesn\[CloseCurlyQuote]t quiet make sense.  I think it should be one \
from analytics.  Finesse3 seems to suggest factor should be 2."
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.904338006865508*^9, 3.904338027529402*^9}, {
  3.92515609832547*^9, 3.925156127788515*^9}, {3.925158940943486*^9, 
  3.92515894873447*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"a2a70586-c86c-4d9c-abc8-\
b907a53b70f8"],

Cell[BoxData[{
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"\[Phi]0", "=", 
   RowBox[{
    FractionBox["\[Omega]0", "c"], "\[CapitalDelta]L"}]}], 
  ";"}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"\[Phi]\[CapitalOmega]", "=", 
   RowBox[{
    FractionBox["\[CapitalOmega]", "c"], 
    RowBox[{"(", 
     RowBox[{"L", "+", "\[CapitalDelta]L"}], ")"}]}]}], 
  ";"}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"\[Phi]\[Omega]", "=", 
   RowBox[{
    FractionBox["\[Omega]", "c"], 
    RowBox[{"(", 
     RowBox[{"L", "+", "\[CapitalDelta]L"}], ")"}]}]}], 
  ";"}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"\[Phi]p\[CapitalOmega]", "=", 
   RowBox[{"\[Phi]0", "+", "\[Phi]\[CapitalOmega]"}]}], 
  ";"}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"\[Phi]m\[CapitalOmega]", "=", 
   RowBox[{"\[Phi]0", "-", "\[Phi]\[CapitalOmega]"}]}], 
  ";"}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"\[Phi]p\[Omega]", "=", 
   RowBox[{"\[Phi]0", "+", "\[Phi]\[Omega]"}]}], ";"}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"\[Phi]m\[Omega]", "=", 
   RowBox[{"\[Phi]0", "-", "\[Phi]\[Omega]"}]}], ";"}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"\[Phi]p\[CapitalOmega]p\[Omega]", "=", 
   RowBox[{"\[Phi]0", "+", "\[Phi]\[CapitalOmega]", "+", "\[Phi]\[Omega]"}]}],
   ";"}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"\[Phi]p\[CapitalOmega]m\[Omega]", "=", 
   RowBox[{"\[Phi]0", "+", "\[Phi]\[CapitalOmega]", "-", "\[Phi]\[Omega]"}]}],
   ";"}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"\[Phi]m\[CapitalOmega]p\[Omega]", "=", 
   RowBox[{"\[Phi]0", "-", "\[Phi]\[CapitalOmega]", "+", "\[Phi]\[Omega]"}]}],
   ";"}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"\[Phi]m\[CapitalOmega]m\[Omega]", "=", 
   RowBox[{"\[Phi]0", "-", "\[Phi]\[CapitalOmega]", "-", "\[Phi]\[Omega]"}]}],
   ";"}]}], "Input",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.904337929813883*^9, 3.904337996879027*^9}, 
   3.904338046268915*^9, {3.925156094276162*^9, 3.925156097031618*^9}, {
   3.9682476385855303`*^9, 3.968247699972033*^9}, {3.968247789012372*^9, 
   3.968247868899981*^9}, {3.968247907502473*^9, 3.9682480046282263`*^9}, {
   3.968248038269595*^9, 3.968248102522676*^9}, 3.968248383609151*^9, {
   3.9682484239863787`*^9, 3.9682484248286324`*^9}},
 CellLabel->
  "In[166]:=",ExpressionUUID->"f87f6154-e954-4052-819e-f5fad72c0b6d"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"factor", "=", 
   AdjustmentBox["1",
    BoxMargins->{{0.07271074755737332, -0.07271074755737332}, {0., 0.}}]}], 
  ";"}]], "Input",
 CellChangeTimes->{3.968250162190987*^9, 3.968253510056362*^9},
 CellLabel->
  "In[177]:=",ExpressionUUID->"76dae88e-f0c0-4fd7-8039-f8bc1d3189bc"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Also remember that the electric field ",
 StyleBox["incident on the end mirror",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " is going to be the one scattered.\nSo the \[Omega]0 and \[CapitalOmega] \
terms should be set only by the input beam, \nbut the \[Omega] terms will \
need the extra end2refl field TF matrix element. "
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.904565502766727*^9, 3.904565538629649*^9}, {
  3.968249694314592*^9, 
  3.968249747195364*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"0d2e27eb-52f9-4e72-a94c-\
75f77785328d"],

Cell["\<\
Because it takes too long for mathematica to simplify, we will use the \
demodulation results of double_demod_derivation.nb and omit any \
time-dependence below.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.968249778715261*^9, 
  3.968249832217029*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"4d3a8427-c914-45ac-900d-\
b05fb4e55dd7"]
}, Open  ]],

